1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,039
Me? Marry you?
Are you out of your mind?

2
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:09,400
Looking for something?

3
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:11,040
This one?

4
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:12,440
Give it back.

5
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:13,600
You gonna hurt me?

6
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,640
Don’t even think about it.

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,080
- You damn mutt tapeworm.
- Sis Nokkaew.

8
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,120
My name’s not Nokkaew.

9
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:22,960
You little, you little,

10
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:28,280
You scared me. I thought you were a ghost.

11
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:29,560
You have a cat?

12
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:30,880
Her name is Pao.

13
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:35,000
Well, if you like it, you can come by often.

14
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:38,320
I came to talk about the land lease.

15
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,800
But I think I’ve already
told you what I want.

16
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:44,720
I know.

17
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:47,320
That’s why I came all the way here.

18
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:48,480
Because I have

19
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:51,520
a few additional conditions.

20
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:55,440
Alright, go ahead.

21
00:00:57,400 --> 00:01:00,120
-First condition, between the two of us,
-Wait.

22
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:02,080
What you’re about to say,

23
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:03,680
it’s something serious, right?

24
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:04,680
Mm.

25
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:07,120
Otherwise, why would I come all
the way here?

26
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:11,080
Then sit and play with Pao for a bit.

27
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,800
Give me a moment.

28
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,000
What are you doing?

29
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,240
Hey,

30
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:22,280
You,you can’t do this.

31
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,520
Get up and talk to me right now.

32
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,760
You said it yourself,

33
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:29,000
what you want to talk about is serious.

34
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:31,440
So I need a quick mental break.

35
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,920
Hey.

36
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,640
But I want to talk and head back quickly.

37
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,800
Do you understand?

38
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:44,320
If you’re in a hurry,
then you can just leave first.

39
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:48,240
Klao,

40
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,960
wake up and talk to me first.

41
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:52,200
How can you just fall asleep like this?

42
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,880
Wake up,don’t mess with me.

43
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:56,840
Do you know my company
renewing your land lease,

44
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,360
It’s worth billions a year.

45
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:01,080
Klao, wake up and talk to me first.

46
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:03,920
How can you mess with me like this?

47
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,320
You could’ve just woken me up nicely.

48
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,440
No need to use force like that.

49
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,320
Si,

50
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,440
Are you okay?

51
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:36,240
Or did you hit your head and lose it?

52
00:05:39,159 --> 00:05:40,240
You,

53
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,720
you,

54
00:05:43,159 --> 00:05:44,320
Si,

55
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,880
I’m fine.

56
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,240
I was just messing with you.

57
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,840
Hey,

58
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,520
can I talk about my business now?

59
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,640
Go ahead.

60
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,760
I’ll marry you.

61
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,640
But I have two more conditions.

62
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,520
First,

63
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:50,200
we’ll just be “engaged” for now,

64
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:52,560
until the time is right.

65
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,400
Second,

66
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,920
if we actually do get married,

67
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:59,400
You’ll have to give me that land

68
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,920
as the bride price.

69
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:05,640
And this “right timing”,

70
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,720
when is that?

71
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,440
When we actually fall in love, I guess.

72
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,400
And if we don’t?

73
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:13,320
Then we just stay “engaged.”

74
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,680
That puts me at a disadvantage.

75
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,840
How are you at a disadvantage?

76
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,200
How?

77
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,720
I don’t see any disadvantage at all.

78
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,600
-Want some?
-No.

79
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,920
I’ve never had it.

80
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,600
And another thing,

81
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,880
being engaged

82
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:31,600
is basically like being in a relationship,

83
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,880
just,

84
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:36,040
a slightly upgraded version of it.

85
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:39,040
Then why don’t we just get married?

86
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,440
If it doesn’t work out, we can just divorce.

87
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,960
That won’t work.

88
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,760
I’d be the one at a loss.

89
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,240
And,

90
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,040
is it really true what you said,

91
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,600
that being engaged is like being a couple?

92
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,640
Mm.

93
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:56,440
Alright.

94
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,440
I agree.

95
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:58,800
Yes!

96
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,640
But,

97
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:04,320
I’ll only renew the lease year by year

98
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:06,760
until we get married.

99
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,520
Then we’ll make changes.

100
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:21,040
Good thing I’m very thorough and careful.

101
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,440
I already had my lawyer prepare everything.

102
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:26,840
Read every clause before you sign, Klao.

103
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:40,320
Hey,

104
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:41,640
What?

105
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,720
What if,

106
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,120
you’re the one who breaks the agreement?

107
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,640
What if you cheat on me first?

108
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:50,760
What then?

109
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,560
I’m a sincere person.

110
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:57,440
My word means everything.

111
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:59,640
I would never do that.

112
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,120
Trust me.

113
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:03,720
Good.

114
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,080
In that case,

115
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,160
hurry up, read it and sign it.

116
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:10,400
So I can take it back to my family.

117
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,720
So they’ll finally stop looking down on me.

118
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,240
You don’t like being looked down on?

119
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,640
Then why did you look down
on me yesterday?

120
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,240
Uh…

121
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,640
Actually,

122
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:27,240
I’m not really like that.

123
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,160
But yesterday in the meeting,

124
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,600
it was really tense.

125
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,600
And I wanted to prove to my family

126
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,520
that I can do it.

127
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:39,720
So I ended up saying something
rude to you, Klao.

128
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,600
I’m sorry.

129
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:43,680
Let me think about it.

130
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,240
Think about what?

131
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,400
Whether,

132
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,920
I should forgive you or not.

133
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,640
Then,

134
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:55,840
you should

135
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,840
hurry up and sign.

136
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,880
(Klaokawee Chaipruek) (Lessor)
(Nattanicha Chueathaiwong) (Witness)

137
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:15,400
Yes! I did it!

138
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:17,360
Thank you, Klao.

139
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:19,040
Since we’re engaged,

140
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:21,840
-when you’re happy, you hug, right?
-Hey, you,

141
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,440
Wait,hey,

142
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,560
It’s just the beginning.

143
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,680
I might need some time

144
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,960
to adjust a little.

145
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,360
Let’s leave it for now.

146
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,520
I’ll get going.

147
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:41,040
My future fiancée.

148
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,040
Bye.

149
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,640
Bye-bye, Pao.

150
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,240
Yes!

151
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:25,040
Is this a forged signature?

152
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,960
Don’t cause more trouble for me, Si.

153
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,120
I already have enough problems.

154
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,200
Dad

155
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,920
why can’t you trust me?

156
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,960
I told you before,

157
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,720
I’d handle everything for you.

158
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:39,880
See?

159
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,440
Klao’s signature

160
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,640
I got it for you.

161
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:48,040
Your father was just asking.
Don’t overthink it.

162
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,880
Honestly, right now,

163
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:51,200
everyone should

164
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:54,000
be applauding my success.

165
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,760
Why does everyone
keep looking down on me?

166
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,640
You mean

167
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:01,240
you’re really going to marry Klao?

168
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,440
Yes.

169
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:04,920
I’ll go along with her conditions.

170
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:06,120
Because I know…

171
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,560
that country girl…

172
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:10,120
there’s no way she can handle me.

173
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,400
Just look at everyone in this house.

174
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,240
Can anyone handle me?

175
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,680
And who is she anyway?

176
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:22,320
Just an ordinary girl in farm clothes,
working the fields.

177
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,600
She made the wrong move…

178
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:25,520
wanting to marry someone like me.

179
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Trust me, in a few days,

180
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,280
she’ll come begging to cancel the deal.

181
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,680
And I’ll use that chance

182
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,120
to trick her

183
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,240
into selling that land to us.

184
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,000
And if she doesn’t…

185
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:39,080
I’ll haunt her

186
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,840
like a curse forever.

187
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:41,920
Just wait.

188
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,440
You’re really cunning, P’Si.

189
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,720
Just thinking about it

190
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,240
gives me chills.

191
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,120
So now…

192
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,320
Dad, Mom… do you see now?

193
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,680
that I’m the one

194
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,440
most suitable to be CEO.

195
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,720
Alright.

196
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:02,240
If it turns out the way you said,

197
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:05,400
then we should really thank you
for your sacrifice.

198
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,120
-Yes, Dad.
-Song,

199
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:10,040
take this document to the lawyer to proceed.

200
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:11,040
Alright?

201
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:13,360
And also check

202
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,840
whether the signature is real.

203
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:15,960
Yes, Dad.

204
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,240
You did great, my dear.

205
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,640
Thank you so much.

206
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:45,040
CEO,

207
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,120
Sujintra.

208
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:50,920
The most perfect CEO in the world.

209
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,840
Jiw is here.

210
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:32,080
Oh, look at that.

211
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,640
Who are you waiting for?

212
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,160
No one.

213
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:39,160
Really, no one?

214
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,760
I just saw you stretching your neck,

215
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,960
like a giraffe.

216
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,840
I said no, didn’t I?

217
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,880
Hey,

218
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:52,920
What was that? You ruined my look.

219
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,760
Sorry, I didn’t mean to.

220
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,840
So, what are you doing here?

221
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,480
I came to get something to eat.

222
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:02,160
I’m starving.

223
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:05,120
I just got back from the hospital.

224
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,520
Go check the cabinet, there’s food in there.

225
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,320
Thanks.

226
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,280
Go on.

227
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,760
-Stop being so nosy.
-It’s not even Songkran yet,

228
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:19,760
and you’re already splashing water around.

229
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:26,680
I smell love in the air.

230
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:29,320
So sweet.

231
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,640
So annoying.

232
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,960
So sweet.

233
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:42,120
Someone’s in love.

234
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:15,000
What time is it?

235
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,840
It’s 11 a.m., Ms. Si.

236
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,400
Did I wake up early today?

237
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,400
(YOUR TIME ZONE)

238
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:37,280
(New York)

239
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:44,040
I should head to the office.

240
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,360
Um, Ms. Si,

241
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,880
-What is it?
-Uh…

242
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:01,960
Well…

243
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,119
Just say it.

244
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:05,720
The chairman said
if you come into the office,

245
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,079
I have to keep
a close eye on you.

246
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:09,920
Don’t let you do anything,
or we’ll get into trouble again.

247
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,520
Where are Dad, Mom, and Song?

248
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:15,040
The chairman, Mrs. Ingorn,
and Ms. Song all went out for a meeting today.

249
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:18,119
-So…
-So…

250
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:19,880
So what?

251
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,839
Are you afraid I’ll ruin the company,
so you’re here to watch me?

252
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,200
It’s not like that.

253
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:26,040
But…

254
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,040
Go do your work.

255
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,680
I won’t do anything.

256
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,960
I don’t want you getting scolded
or in trouble because of me.

257
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:38,040
Thank you, Si.

258
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,760
-Um, Si,
-Hm?

259
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:43,000
The chairman said these
credit card bills from accounting,

260
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,640
you have to pay all of them yourself.

261
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:45,640
What?

262
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,160
All of them.

263
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:02,760
Hello, Dad,

264
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:06,440
Why are you doing this to me?
Where am I supposed to get the money?

265
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:07,920
Dad,

266
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Hello?

267
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,280
Dad,

268
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,720
Dad,

269
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,760
You damn parasite.

270
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,640
You damn parasite.

271
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,280
Why did you cut me off like that?

272
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,920
Are you trying to die?

273
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:56,800
And you? Why are you driving so fast?
In a hurry or what?

274
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,240
Wanna race me?

275
00:18:58,520 --> 00:18:59,520
You in?

276
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,320
Where’s your boss?

277
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:04,040
"Where’s your boss?"

278
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,360
Where’s your boss?

279
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,920
Right here.

280
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,200
-Right here.
-You money-grubber.

281
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,520
-You only ask for money when you see me.
-Here it is. So, wanna see my boss or not?

282
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,240
-Give it.
-Let’s go.

283
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,760
Hurry up.

284
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,600
Do it properly.

285
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:19,840
Here.

286
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:22,960
Now that you’ve got the money,
tell me where your boss is.

287
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,120
Come on, it’s hot.

288
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:26,320
Where is my boss?

289
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:30,840
Right here in my heart.

290
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:34,760
Over there.

291
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,200
The only handsome one around.

292
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:39,360
My boss is seriously cool.

293
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:40,520
-Over there.
-Oh my god.

294
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,720
Wait here, I’ll be right back.

295
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,400
I seriously don’t get it.

296
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:14,600
Someone who owns land, earning rent

297
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,160
in the billions every year,

298
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,760
yet lives like this?

299
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:21,360
It’s so hot,will my skin be okay?

300
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,520
I’m getting burned.

301
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:24,840
I’ll need a full vitamin
drip when I get back.

302
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,280
So annoying.

303
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:29,520
If it weren’t for my pride,

304
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:32,120
I wouldn’t put myself through this.

305
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,160
What are you looking at?

306
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:38,760
You’re grumbling nonstop.

307
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:40,840
What do you want now?

308
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,760
My future wife.

309
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:55,680
Out of nowhere, my dad ordered
someone to watch me at the office

310
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:56,800
while he’s away.

311
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,440
Guess he’s afraid I’ll cause trouble again.

312
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,680
And normally,

313
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:06,120
my dad pays my credit
card bills every month,

314
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,000
but suddenly he stopped.

315
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,720
How could he do this to me?

316
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,800
Do you know how annoyed I am?

317
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:14,480
So annoyed I just want to scream it out.

318
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:17,040
Then if you want to scream, just scream.

319
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,440
I...

320
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:23,120
I can really scream?

321
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:24,640
Of course.

322
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:26,920
You can scream as
loud as you want because

323
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,760
no one around here will hear you.

324
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,360
Really?

325
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:33,560
One

326
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,760
two, three

327
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:48,040
Do you feel better now?

328
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:50,760
No.

329
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:53,320
And...

330
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:55,400
what do you usually do

331
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:57,200
when you’re annoyed?

332
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:58,960
Well...

333
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,560
Normally I

334
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:02,320
go shopping, get my nails done,

335
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:03,880
do my hair, go to the spa.

336
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:06,040
Or if I’m really annoyed,

337
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:08,400
I just buy a new car.

338
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,640
Then why didn’t you do that today?

339
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Well...

340
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:12,960
I don’t really know.

341
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,760
I was so annoyed, I just kept driving,

342
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,240
and before I knew it, I ended up here.

343
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:20,360
Then I ran into that
damn idiot who cut me off.

344
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,920
Hey, hey,

345
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,920
I think

346
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,240
your high heels

347
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:29,320
-aren’t suitable for walking on a rice field path.
-Hey, what are you doing?

348
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,920
Don’t tell me you want me to wear those.

349
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,760
No way.

350
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,840
It’s going to itch like crazy.

351
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:38,080
If you fall face-first,

352
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:39,680
you won’t just itch,

353
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,240
you’ll get hurt too.

354
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:45,840
Or you could ride on my back.

355
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:47,880
Uh…

356
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,720
I’ll just walk.

357
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:52,720
Then…

358
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,720
what will you wear?

359
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:55,920
Don’t tell me

360
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,520
you’re going to wear my heels.

361
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,920
I can walk barefoot.

362
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,440
Wait,

363
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:09,360
Okay.

364
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:22,040
-Are there bugs in here?
-No.

365
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,200
Come on, let’s go.

366
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,640
If you want to keep complaining, go ahead.

367
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:32,760
I’m listening.

368
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:35,240
So yeah,

369
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:36,360
you know,

370
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,600
not only did my dad make me
pay all my credit cards myself,

371
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:41,280
but after that,

372
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:44,320
he froze every single one of my cards.

373
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:46,160
I’ve never even gotten
a salary, think about it.

374
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:48,560
Now I have to pay myself,
where am I supposed to get the money?

375
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:50,800
My dad,

376
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,400
he gives everything to Song.

377
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:54,160
Even though I’m the older sister,

378
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:56,920
my parents have never paid attention to me.

379
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:01,040
Do you feel better now?

380
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:03,440
No.

381
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:07,560
Then let’s go home.

382
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:09,920
I’ll cook something nice for you.

383
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,080
It’s okay.

384
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:12,920
This place is countryside, so...

385
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:17,400
It’s rural out here.

386
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:18,960
There’s probably nothing to eat.

387
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:22,160
If anything, it’s frogs, crickets, or snakes.

388
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,680
I can’t eat that. No thanks.

389
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:33,560
Eat more, Jon.

390
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:35,720
Oh, sis…

391
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:37,560
why are you back so early today?

392
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:39,960
Woo-hoo.

393
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:42,560
We meet again, Miss Nokkaew.

394
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,680
I thought you already went home.

395
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:46,360
Jiw…

396
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,400
go watch over Pidpee and Muedmon for me.

397
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:50,080
Got it.

398
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,200
Are you Miss Nokkaew or a fish?

399
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:57,080
-So many scales.
-None of your business.

400
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:02,840
The car’s fast because I tuned the engine.

401
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,360
Who are they?

402
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,040
Pidpee and Muedmon.

403
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:14,040
They’re a mother and calf buffalo in the field.

404
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,760
I just bought their lives back.

405
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:19,480
You’re kind of mean with those names.

406
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:23,480
Wait…

407
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:25,320
then why did you hire

408
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:28,080
that annoying kid to work for you?

409
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,400
From the way he looks,

410
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,200
he seems pretty clueless.

411
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:32,880
Who knows, maybe he’s on drugs.

412
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:35,000
He’s not on drugs.

413
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:36,680
Even if he looks like it.

414
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,960
What would you know?

415
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:42,000
You spend all day in the fields, you don’t get kids.

416
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,480
Jiw has end-stage kidney disease.

417
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:49,000
He has to go for dialysis almost every day.

418
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:51,160
He doesn’t have parents.

419
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:54,200
I felt sorry for him, so I let him stay and help out.

420
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:57,280
So when you see him like this,

421
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:59,160
just be a little kind to him.

422
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,080
He’s just being playful with you.

423
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:02,960
He’s actually a good kid, it’s nothing serious.

424
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,120
Sir…

425
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:18,760
someone said

426
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,400
Si came to the office,

427
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,360
then stormed out angrily.

428
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:24,760
Because you ordered her not to do anything.

429
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:27,080
Yes, I gave that order.

430
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,280
Isn’t that a bit too harsh?

431
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:32,080
She’s still our daughter.

432
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,320
And she’s sacrificing for us,

433
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,960
agreeing to marry Klao.

434
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:40,680
She’s not truly willing.

435
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,880
And I don’t like it either,

436
00:26:43,120 --> 00:26:45,080
that she plans to deceive her.

437
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:47,680
You know I’m a straightforward person.

438
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,560
And besides,

439
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,760
our daughter isn’t a child anymore,

440
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:54,280
who needs to be indulged like before.

441
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:57,840
-But she still agreed to…
-Can I get back to work?

442
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:04,920
Smells so good, looks delicious.

443
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:06,280
It’s almost done.

444
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:15,320
Sis…

445
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:19,960
-Sis…
-Who’s calling me?

446
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:22,160
What is it?

447
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:25,400
Where did Klao go?

448
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:28,600
Oh, she went out to buy something.
She’ll be back soon.

449
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:31,040
And…

450
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:33,800
what are you cooking? It smells great.

451
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:39,760
Here, grilled field rat.

452
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:41,800
Field rat?

453
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,560
What’s wrong?

454
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:47,240
Hey, where are you going?

455
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:48,320
Aren’t you eating first?

456
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:50,360
It’s fine, I’m full.

457
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,480
I have something to do, I’ll head back first.

458
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,680
What?

459
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,760
-P’Duean…
-Smells great.

460
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:59,320
-Yes?
-Please help me with this too.

461
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:00,400
Sure.

462
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:05,920
They’re all so plump. Jackpot.

463
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:09,680
Where are you going?

464
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:11,680
Stay and eat with me first.

465
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,560
I’m not hungry.

466
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:16,800
Eat first,

467
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:17,800
then go.

468
00:28:18,080 --> 00:28:19,920
Eat field rat?

469
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:21,560
Who could eat that?

470
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:22,640
I’m going to throw up.

471
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,640
You can eat it yourself.

472
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,960
Didn’t you say

473
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,560
being engaged is like being
in a relationship?

474
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,600
Couples should eat together.

475
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,880
Are these your siblings?

476
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,080
Yeah.

477
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,560
The one at the bottom is P’Kant.

478
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:02,720
He’s the eldest brother.

479
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:05,160
He’s in politics, and his wife
is a member of parliament.

480
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:06,920
The third one,

481
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:09,280
his name is Karn, and he’s married too.

482
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:10,760
His wife is a provincial governor.

483
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:13,240
And the youngest brother is Kitt.

484
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:14,760
His wife is a doctor.

485
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:15,960
As for me…

486
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:17,280
P’Klao.

487
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:19,360
has a high-society wife.

488
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:22,560
Just a “fiancée” for now.

489
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:33,120
Here it comes, here it comes.

490
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:36,000
Special menu.

491
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,480
Here you go.

492
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,280
Here.

493
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,480
Grilled field rat.

494
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:46,280
And this dish, highly recommended…

495
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:49,080
stir-fried basil frog.

496
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:50,920
Hey, hey…

497
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:52,960
this one is a must-try.

498
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,760
Spicy boiled frog.

499
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:59,640
Here, I’ll serve you some rice.

500
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,560
This is sticky rice.

501
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:14,160
Huh?

502
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,800
You really went and teased her.

503
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:25,480
She kept looking down on us
as country people,

504
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:27,080
so she had it coming.

505
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,760
But she’s kind of pitiful.

506
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:41,040
Are you okay?

507
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:43,280
I’m not.

508
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,640
I’m going home.

509
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:47,960
Finish your food first.

510
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:49,800
That’s rude.

511
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:51,160
P’Duean will be upset.

512
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:54,480
How is anyone supposed to eat this?
What even are these dishes?

513
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:05,080
There are shrimp here?

514
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,160
A food truck passed by,

515
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:08,560
so I bought some.

516
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:12,680
You should’ve told me there
was something good like this earlier.

517
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:14,880
But…

518
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:17,040
could you…

519
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:19,400
clear that plate and…

520
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:22,600
bring me a new plate and utensils?

521
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:25,600
Otherwise I might throw up again.

522
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:28,880
-P’Duean…
-Yes?

523
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:30,080
Coming.

524
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,080
Here.

525
00:31:32,080 --> 00:31:33,200
Wait a moment.

526
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:37,280
Here, all set.

527
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,960
Much better.

528
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,400
That’s better.

529
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:56,040
You shouldn’t look down on us
like that again.

530
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,560
This is how we live and eat.

531
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:00,360
It’s the countryside way of life.

532
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:03,560
Even if it’s different from
what you’re used to,

533
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:06,360
it doesn’t mean it’s wrong or strange.

534
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,960
I understand now.

535
00:32:16,360 --> 00:32:17,360
Klao…

536
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:19,800
there’s something
I’ve been wanting to ask you.

537
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,840
You live in Suphan Buri,

538
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,160
so why

539
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,680
don’t you have the accent?

540
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:27,680
Because my grandparents are from Bangkok,

541
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:29,960
and they moved here
when my dad was still a kid.

542
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:32,280
So no one in the family speaks with that accent.

543
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:36,240
But you own so many plots of land…

544
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:39,160
why live in a place like this?

545
00:32:58,440 --> 00:32:59,440
Well…

546
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:01,120
because I like it.

547
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,680
I think it suits you.

548
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:10,920
What about you?

549
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:13,000
Why are you so spoiled?

550
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:16,680
How well do you even know me?

551
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:18,840
Not even a week.

552
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:19,880
See?

553
00:33:41,120 --> 00:33:42,480
Actually,

554
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:46,560
my parents spoiled me
since I was little,

555
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:49,520
treated me like a princess.

556
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:52,360
I didn’t have to do anything,
just dress up and stay home.

557
00:33:53,320 --> 00:33:54,440
But suddenly,

558
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:55,480
they just

559
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:57,880
stopped spoiling me out of nowhere.

560
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:01,080
So who’s really at fault here,
don’t you think?

561
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:04,360
And besides,

562
00:34:04,640 --> 00:34:07,080
you’re my fiancée.

563
00:34:07,600 --> 00:34:09,480
You should be on my side.

564
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:12,360
Never mind.

565
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:14,360
If something is wrong,

566
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:16,480
I won’t lie and say it’s right.

567
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:19,280
But if you feel like something’s missing,

568
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:21,239
I’ll take care of you

569
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:23,040
until you forget

570
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:24,360
you ever lacked anything.

571
00:34:30,800 --> 00:34:31,880
You…

572
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:33,960
say such strange things.

573
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:41,280
Are you serious,
or is the situation forcing you?

574
00:34:43,199 --> 00:34:45,159
I mean,

575
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:47,120
when we actually love each other,

576
00:34:47,159 --> 00:34:49,120
and when we get married,

577
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:50,320
not now.

578
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:51,480
Mm-hmm.

579
00:35:03,120 --> 00:35:05,080
If you’re done eating, just leave it here.

580
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:06,480
Duean will come clear it.

581
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:08,680
The village head called me
to talk about something.

582
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,080
Seems urgent.

583
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:34,280
Why won’t the car start?

584
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:55,480
Where did she go?

585
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,880
You damn leech.

586
00:36:10,240 --> 00:36:11,280
Oh, hey.

587
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,160
So which one am I…

588
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:16,160
a pork tapeworm or a beef tapeworm?

589
00:36:16,200 --> 00:36:18,160
That depends on my mood.

590
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,680
But to me,

591
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:23,240
you’re the one and only
Miss Nokkaew in my heart.

592
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:26,160
That’ll never change, 100%.

593
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:28,600
Where are you going?

594
00:36:29,080 --> 00:36:30,920
To find a girl.

595
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:32,000
Wait a sec.

596
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:35,480
What’s with her?

597
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:39,200
Hurry up, you’re wasting time.

598
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:48,280
Whoa, this time,

599
00:36:48,320 --> 00:36:51,360
Miss Nokkaew is really generous.

600
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:54,480
What do you want me to do?

601
00:36:57,440 --> 00:37:00,360
Jiw has end-stage kidney disease.

602
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,760
So when you see him like this,

603
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,680
just be a little kind to him.

604
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:08,760
Here…

605
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,080
this is extra.

606
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:18,080
What are you up to this time?

607
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:21,760
You’re acting strange.

608
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:23,960
Normally you’re stingy even with 200.

609
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:26,280
But now it’s 2,000…sweet deal.

610
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:28,360
So what’s your plan?

611
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,720
Go get your boss for me.

612
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,880
Tell her my car won’t start.

613
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:35,640
Maybe I hit something
while following you to the field.

614
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,080
Hey, don’t blame me.

615
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:42,080
I’ll handle it for you, nice and smooth.

616
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:47,880
How is it?

617
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,160
It can’t be fixed.

618
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,120
I’ll contact the repair shop myself.

619
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:53,080
Okay, thank you.

620
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:54,480
No problem.

621
00:37:57,960 --> 00:37:58,960
Hey…

622
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:00,640
your car can’t be fixed.

623
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:01,680
What?

624
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:03,560
But I’ll have it towed,

625
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:06,360
and someone will return it to your house.

626
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:07,560
Then how

627
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:10,000
am I supposed to get home today?

628
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:21,000
You have a car like this?

629
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,280
I thought

630
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:25,640
I’d have to ride that junk back home.

631
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:27,640
That one’s my car.

632
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:29,200
Its name is “Old Uncle.”

633
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:31,720
And this one belongs to my sister-in-law.

634
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:33,920
“Old Uncle” really lives up to the name.

635
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,480
And…

636
00:38:39,080 --> 00:38:40,400
don’t you want to change

637
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:41,400
that outfit?

638
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:44,040
Why should I?

639
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:46,320
I’m just driving you home.

640
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:49,720
If I say it,

641
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,000
you’ll say I’m looking down
on you again.

642
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:53,920
But you have to understand,

643
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,240
in today’s society,

644
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:56,560
it’s unavoidable

645
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:59,200
that people judge others
by how they dress.

646
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:02,520
If you don’t respect yourself,

647
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:04,640
who will respect you?

648
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:09,000
You can be yourself
in your own safe zone,

649
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,600
but once you’re out in society,

650
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:14,200
you need to know what’s appropriate
and what’s not, right?

651
00:39:15,800 --> 00:39:16,800
You…

652
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:19,320
you seem pretty thoughtful.

653
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:20,680
But…

654
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:21,920
why?

655
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,000
Why what?

656
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:25,680
Well, if

657
00:39:25,720 --> 00:39:28,920
someone makes fun of how I dress,

658
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:31,120
you’d join in too, right?

659
00:39:32,040 --> 00:39:33,400
Of course.

660
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,400
Let’s go.

661
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,320
I’m heading off.

662
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:42,240
Hey, Si…

663
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,440
where’s your car?

664
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:45,640
Who dropped you off?

665
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:49,480
Si…

666
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:53,600
I’m asking you,

667
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,320
who dropped you off?

668
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:57,520
Answer me.

669
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:01,240
The one I’m seeing.

670
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:03,040
I knew it.

671
00:41:04,080 --> 00:41:05,200
Si, you…

672
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:08,400
you’ve already signed
a marriage contract with Klao,

673
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:11,200
and now you’re staying with your fling?

674
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:14,600
If Klao finds out

675
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:16,840
and cancels the contract,
what will you do?

676
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:18,800
Mom.

677
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:21,840
You only care about the contract.

678
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,760
You don’t care about me at all.

679
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,200
Oh, Si.

680
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,360
Darling.

681
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:30,800
Get the car ready.

682
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:34,800
Where are you going?

683
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:37,480
Uh...

684
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,040
Well...

685
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:41,920
-Uh...
-Let’s go, darling. It’s late.

686
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,120
Two.

687
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,480
I asked where you’re going.

688
00:41:45,640 --> 00:41:47,040
Well...

689
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,360
Dad is taking the team

690
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:51,120
handling the land lease
contract out for a meal.

691
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:53,920
Because we’ve worked hard for a year.

692
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:55,200
And you…

693
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:56,720
want to come with us?

694
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,200
Worked hard for a year?

695
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:03,600
Everyone’s going to celebrate

696
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,600
without me?

697
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:08,920
I’m the one who made this happen.

698
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,440
Si, no one thinks that.

699
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:16,400
Your dad saw you weren’t home,

700
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:18,840
and it just happened that everyone

701
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:20,840
was available.

702
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:23,720
Just go shower, get dressed,
and come with us.

703
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:29,520
I know.

704
00:42:29,720 --> 00:42:32,320
I’m someone no one in this house wants.

705
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:35,560
But I didn’t think Dad, Mom, and Two

706
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:37,600
would hate me this much.

707
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:49,120
Just let her be.

708
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:52,120
If she comes, she’ll just cause trouble

709
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:54,320
and say things people don’t like again.

710
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:56,200
Let’s go.

711
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:02,040
(YOUR TIME ZONE)

712
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:06,000
(New York)

713
00:44:35,120 --> 00:44:36,440
Can I sit here?

714
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:42,080
Please give me some personal space.

715
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:22,720
Hello, Uncle Headman.

716
00:46:25,560 --> 00:46:26,560
Yes.

717
00:46:34,880 --> 00:46:37,280
I don’t know if something’s wrong with her.

718
00:46:37,280 --> 00:46:38,880
Hurry up.

719
00:46:38,960 --> 00:46:40,600
I have to go now.

720
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:49,480
Si.

721
00:46:50,440 --> 00:46:51,440
You...

722
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:52,880
You...

723
00:46:54,720 --> 00:46:55,720
What?

724
00:46:56,840 --> 00:46:59,200
Are you okay? Why did you stop here?

725
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:03,200
I’m sleepy.

726
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:05,160
I couldn’t drive anymore, so I stopped.

727
00:47:06,160 --> 00:47:07,920
You scared me.

728
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:09,360
The headman called and said

729
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:11,680
he knocked many times,

730
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:13,200
but you didn’t wake up.

731
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:18,920
How did he know to call you?

732
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:21,400
A fancy car was parked here,

733
00:47:21,440 --> 00:47:23,560
so he thought you were my friend.

734
00:47:23,600 --> 00:47:26,480
No one around here drives a car like this.

735
00:47:26,680 --> 00:47:28,120
Let’s go. Let’s go home.

736
00:47:28,120 --> 00:47:29,200
I’ll drive.

737
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:30,960
Here.

738
00:47:39,720 --> 00:47:40,840
Come on.

739
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:41,960
Mm.

740
00:48:36,600 --> 00:48:37,600
You.

741
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:40,640
You’ve been adjusting the seat up and down,
I’m getting dizzy.

742
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:42,080
Well...

743
00:48:42,440 --> 00:48:44,720
You change cars every day, and I...

744
00:48:44,720 --> 00:48:46,560
don’t know how to use this one.

745
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:49,040
Alright, alright, okay.

746
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:50,600
Go, go, go.

747
00:48:57,440 --> 00:48:58,840
Let’s go.

748
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,200
You.

749
00:49:30,800 --> 00:49:32,720
I think I’ll stay at a hotel.

750
00:49:32,800 --> 00:49:35,280
You’re this sleepy, can you even drive?

751
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:37,440
Then you take me.

752
00:49:39,040 --> 00:49:40,040
What?

753
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:42,440
Why should I be the one bothered?

754
00:49:44,200 --> 00:49:45,400
Come on.

755
00:49:45,440 --> 00:49:47,720
This house may be a Thai-style house,

756
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:50,040
but I just built it a few years ago.

757
00:49:50,280 --> 00:49:52,560
It’s not some hundred-year inheritance.

758
00:49:52,880 --> 00:49:54,160
There are no ghosts.

759
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:55,440
I was just teasing.

760
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:58,120
Come on, let’s go inside.

761
00:49:58,160 --> 00:49:59,680
It’s late, we have to wake up early.

762
00:49:59,680 --> 00:50:01,240
It’s scary.

763
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:22,600
Come on.

764
00:50:23,880 --> 00:50:24,960
Here.

765
00:50:26,720 --> 00:50:28,040
Your room?

766
00:50:28,600 --> 00:50:29,600
Yes.

767
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:32,000
You want me to sleep with you?

768
00:50:32,040 --> 00:50:35,440
What, or do you want to sleep
in the guest room?

769
00:50:35,920 --> 00:50:36,920
Do you?

770
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:45,240
Are you going to shower?

771
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:48,240
Yeah.

772
00:50:48,360 --> 00:50:49,360
But...

773
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:51,360
I don’t have any clothes.

774
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:53,320
I’ll get you some.

775
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:04,800
Here.

776
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:18,440
You.

777
00:51:19,720 --> 00:51:20,720
Hmm?

778
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:23,640
Don’t peek. I’m getting undressed.

779
00:51:24,920 --> 00:51:27,320
Who showers with the door open?

780
00:51:27,840 --> 00:51:30,080
I’m scared of ghosts.

781
00:51:33,640 --> 00:51:34,880
Don’t look.

782
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:36,040
Mm.

783
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:54,320
You idiot.

784
00:51:54,360 --> 00:51:56,240
I told you not to peek.

785
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,120
Pervert.

786
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:04,520
If I wasn’t scared of ghosts,
I’d splash you with water.

787
00:52:06,680 --> 00:52:08,520
-You.
-Hmm?

788
00:52:08,560 --> 00:52:09,760
What are you doing?

789
00:52:09,800 --> 00:52:12,800
Say something. Don’t be quiet, I’m scared.

790
00:52:12,920 --> 00:52:15,440
Then what do you want me to say?

791
00:52:16,960 --> 00:52:18,520
If you won’t talk,

792
00:52:18,840 --> 00:52:20,520
you can play some music.

793
00:52:24,440 --> 00:52:27,600
(The Melon Farm Girl by Got Jakraphan)

794
00:53:10,400 --> 00:53:11,560
Hey, you.

795
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:15,080
Don’t you dare try anything with me.

796
00:53:15,560 --> 00:53:17,480
I can box, just so you know.

797
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:19,480
If you try anything,

798
00:53:19,800 --> 00:53:21,480
I’ll elbow you for sure.

799
00:53:23,360 --> 00:53:24,400
Sure.

800
00:53:24,440 --> 00:53:25,600
I’m scared.

801
00:53:26,920 --> 00:53:28,880
Can we sleep now?

802
00:53:29,960 --> 00:53:31,960
Then turn off the lights.

803
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:38,720
Quiet, and take this chicken away.

804
00:54:38,720 --> 00:54:42,600
Or I’ll snap its neck and grill it, just wait.

805
00:54:43,040 --> 00:54:46,400
Jon, I’m sorry. I didn’t mean it.

806
00:54:47,760 --> 00:54:49,280
How do you wear this?

807
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:51,960
Step in the middle and take off your clothes.

808
00:54:52,000 --> 00:54:54,160
-Don’t look at me when I’m naked, okay?
-Mm.

809
00:54:54,160 --> 00:54:56,800
See you in Thailand. I’m going back soon.

810
00:54:56,800 --> 00:54:59,680
I see you staring at your phone all day.

811
00:54:59,680 --> 00:55:01,520
Are you talking to someone?

812
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:08,520
You.

813
00:55:08,520 --> 00:55:10,120
Yeah, yeah.

814
00:55:11,560 --> 00:55:13,440
- Hey.
- One more time.

815
00:55:13,440 --> 00:55:15,200
What are you doing? I’m soaked.

816
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:16,240
I’m soaked.

817
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:18,560
So sweet.

818
00:55:21,440 --> 00:55:23,600
(Really soaked, no stand-in)

819
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:25,480
(Hang in there)

820
00:55:25,560 --> 00:55:26,840
Okay, cut.

821
00:55:27,280 --> 00:55:30,000
- You were tense when you walked just now.
- Not anymore.

822
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:31,760
(Scream)

823
00:55:32,280 --> 00:55:35,360
(That scream is opera level)

824
00:55:36,880 --> 00:55:38,200
(Grabbed it like they knew each other)
